```
const API_URL = 'https://api.openai.com/v1/images/generations';

const generateImage = async (prompt, apiKey) => {
  const response = await fetch(API_URL, {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'application/json',
      'Authorization': `Bearer ${apiKey}`,
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      prompt: prompt,
      n: 1,
      size: '1024x1024',
      response_format: 'url',
    }),
  });
  const json = await response.json();
  return json.data[0].url;
};
```

You can then use the `generateImage` function by passing in a prompt string and your API key, like so:

```
const prompt = 'A logo for A D H D that represents unity, education, and innovation';
const apiKey = 'YOUR_API_KEY';
const imageUrl = await generateImage(prompt, apiKey);
```

This will return a URL to the generated image that you can use to display the image in your application.

