To use DALL·E, you will need to make an HTTP POST request to the DALL·E API endpoint, which is:

https://api.openai.com/v1/images/generations

You will need to include your API key in the request header, as well as the prompt in the request body. Here is an example of how you can make a request using the fetch function in JavaScript:

```
fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/images/generations', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'Authorization': 'Bearer YOUR_API_KEY',
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    'prompt': 'YOUR_PROMPT',
    'model': 'image-alpha-001',
  }),
})
  .then((response) => response.json())
  .then((data) => console.log(data))
  .catch((error) => console.error(error));
```

Replace `YOUR_API_KEY` with your actual API key, and `YOUR_PROMPT` with your desired prompt. You can also specify a different model by replacing `image-alpha-001` with the name of the model you want to use.

