    <title>World War LOL</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('static', filename='style.css') }}">
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/socket.io/4.0.1/socket.io.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <audio autoplay>
        <source src="{{ url_for('static', filename='your_audio_file.mp3') }}" type="audio/mpeg">
    </audio>

    <div id="terminal">
        <textarea id="output" readonly></textarea>
        <input id="input" type="text" placeholder="Enter command...">
    </div>

    <script src="{{ url_for('static', filename='script.js') }}"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

#### `static/style.css`:
```css
body {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    background-color: #000;
    color: #0f0;
}

#terminal {
    width: 80%;
    margin: 2rem auto;
}

#output {
    width: 100%;
    height: 300px;
    background-color: #000;
    color: #0f0;
    border: none;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow: auto;
}

#input {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: #000;
    color: #0f0;
    border: none;
    padding: 0.5rem;
}
```

#### `static/script.js`:
```javascript
const socket = io.connect('http://' + document.domain + ':' + location.port);

document.getElementById('input').addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
    if (e.key === 'Enter') {
        let command = this.value;
        socket.emit('send_command', {command: command});
        this.value = '';
    }
});

socket.on('output', function(data) {
    let output = document.getElementById('output');
    output.value += '> ' + data.command + '\n' + data.result + '\n';
    output.scrollTop = output.scrollHeight;
});
```

### 3. Backend

Update `app.py`:
```python
# ... [previous code]

from subprocess import Popen, PIPE

@socketio.on('send_command')
def handle_command(data):
    command = data['command']
    process = Popen(command.split(), stdout=PIPE, stderr=PIPE)
    stdout, stderr = process.communicate()
    result = stdout.decode() if stdout else stderr.decode()
    socketio.emit('output', {'command': command, 'result': result})
```

This setup will give you a basic terminal interface on your webpage. When you enter a command in the input field and press Enter, the command will be executed on the server, and the output will be displayed in the textarea.

**Note**: This setup is for demonstration purposes and is not secure. Executing arbitrary commands from user input can expose your server to various security risks. If you plan to deploy this in a production environment, you should implement proper security measures and sanitize user input.

